    "description: An\n...\nis now available. On\n...\n, 20\n...\n6, Abundia\n...\nImpact Group announced a\n...\n-year strategic agreement\n...\n* Abundia signed a 10-year deal for plastic waste feedstock, covering about half the Cedar Port plant\u2019s needs.\n* The agreement marks a key step toward commercial execution of Abundia\u2019s waste-to-fuels platform and future facilities.\n...\nAn update from Abundia Global Impact Group ( [(AGIG)](https://www.tipranks.com/stocks/agig) ) is now available.\n...\nOn June 9, 2026, [Abundia Global Impact Group](https://www.tipranks.com/stocks/agig) announced a 10-year strategic agreement with Frankfort Plastics to supply 40,000 tons per year of polyolefin plastic waste to its Cedar Port Waste to Fuels facility in Texas. The contracted volume represents about 50% of the expected feedstock requirement for Abundia\u2019s first Cedar Port plant, supporting production of renewable fuels and low-carbon chemicals from hard-to-recycle plastics.\n...\nManagement highlighted that securing long-term feedstock is a key milestone in shifting the Cedar Port project from development toward commercial execution and may also underpin future facilities in the company\u2019s rollout plan. The deal leverages Frankfort Plastics\u2019 established capability in processing low-grade plastic film and comes as Abundia nears completion of Phase 1 construction at Cedar Port, including its Innovation Center and operational headquarters, strengthening its positioning in the emerging waste-to-fuels market. \n\nThe most recent analyst rating on [(AGIG)](https://www.tipranks.com/stocks/agig) stock is a Buy \nwith a $6.00 price target. \nTo see the full list of analyst forecasts on Abundia Global Impact Group stock, \nsee the AGIG [Stock Forecast page](https://www.tipranks.com/stocks/agig/forecast). \n\n**\n...\nAbundia Global Impact Group, Inc. is a Houston-based low-carbon energy company focused on converting waste plastics and biomass into drop-in renewable fuels and low-carbon chemical feedstocks. Listed on the NYSE American under the ticker AGIG and formerly known as Houston American Energy Corp., it is developing commercial-scale facilities, with its flagship Cedar Port project positioned within the Gulf Coast\u2019s energy and chemical hub.\n...\nThe Cedar Port location provides Abundia with access to regional feedstock supply chains, upgrading partners, and end markets for its low-carbon products. The company aims to build a commercial waste-to-fuel platform that integrates advanced recycling technologies with existing industrial infrastructure to serve energy and chemical customers. \n\n**Average Trading Volume:** 270,705\n...\nhttps://www\n...\ntipranks.com/\n...\n/tipranksnewsdesk\"},\"\n...\n\":\"https://www.google.com/search\n...\n\",\"tickerSymbol\":\""
